result.execSummary:
The defendant KYLE E JOHNSON was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

records.addlTxt: Count 3
Count 1

1:16 PM Defendant KYLE E JOHNSON in court.  Attorney Michael J Kapelis in court for KYLE E JOHNSON.  Attorney Gerise Marie Laspisa in court for State of Wisconsin. Court recites offer - in exchange for plea to count 1 and 3, State will recommend jail, costs and DNA for count 1 and count 3, probation, AODA, costs, DNA and conditions.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant. Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights. Court goes over the elements of each offense. Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty. Court instructs defendant regarding deportation. (If felony) Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions. 

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST. Court finds the plea is made knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently. Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea. Court finds the defendant guilty on count 1 and count 3 and will dismiss and read in count 2 and count 4. Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today. Sentencing statement by DA Laspisa. Sentencing statement by Atty Kapelis. No statement by the defendant. Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST on both traffic cases. Court finds the defendant guilty on both traffic cases. Assess the forfeiture.

Court sentences the defendant to:

Count 1 

-20 Days Jail straight. Sentence is to commence within 60 days.  Court does not grant huber, out-of-county service or out-of-county travel. 
-Court Costs. Court grants the defendant 60 days to pay or call the Clerk of Courts Office (920-294-4142) to set-up a payment plan. 
-Defendant is to submit a DNA Sample.  


Count 3

-SWD, and places the defendant on probation for 1 year.

-Court Costs. To be paid to the Clerk of Courts office. To be paid to the Clerk of Courts office.  Monies are to be paid during the term (1 year) of probation.  Failure to pay may result in the suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency. 
-Defendant is to submit a DNA Sample. 
-AODA and any follow-up. 
-Any recommendations by the agent.
-Defendant is to maintain absolute sobriety - not to possess or consume any alcohol, illegal drugs or prescription drugs without a valid prescription.  You may be randomly tested for compliance. 


Court grants the defendant 19 days jail credit to be applied to count 1. 


Court adjourned at 1:30 PM.
